</ast>

<description>

The Clients page displays a data table of all clients with columns for Name (clickable link), Account No., External ID, Status (Pending as yellow chip, Active as green chip, Closed as gray chip, Rejected as red chip, Withdrawn as orange chip), Office, and Staff. A search field allows searching by name, account number, external ID, or mobile number, and a filter bar supports filtering by status. Two buttons at the top-right provide "Import Client" (opens the Bulk Import page) and "Create Client." The Bulk Import page allows downloading a client Excel template, uploading a completed file, and displays an import history table with columns for Name, Import Time, End Time, Completed, Total Records, Success Count, Failure Count, and Download.

The Create Client form is a multi-step wizard. Step 1 (General Details) contains Office (required), Legal Form, First Name (required), Middle Name, Last Name (required), Date of Birth, Gender, Staff, Mobile Number, Email Address, Client Type, Client Classification, External ID (must be unique), Submitted On (required), Is Staff checkbox, Active checkbox, and Open Savings Account option. Step 2 covers Address Details. Step 3 covers Family Members. Step 4 covers Identifiers (Document Type and Document Key). Clicking "Submit" creates the client in Pending status.

The Client Detail page displays the client name, account number, status badge, activation date, and office. Action buttons change based on status: Pending offers Activate (requires Activation Date, which must not be before submission date), Edit, Reject (with reason), and Withdraw (with reason); Active offers Edit, Transfer Client (destination office required — same office is blocked), Close (closure reason required — cannot close with active accounts), Add Charge, New Loan, New Savings, and New Share Account; Closed offers Reactivate; Rejected and Withdrawn have no actions. Tabs on the detail page show General, Accounts (sub-tabs for Loans, Savings, Shares, Fixed Deposits, Recurring Deposits), Identifiers (Document Type and Key with add/remove — duplicates are prevented), Family Members, Notes, and Documents.

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | View Client from Clients list | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: View Client | on_success: navigates to Client Detail page
WF-002 | Open Bulk Import from Clients page | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Import Client | on_success: navigates to Bulk_Import_Page
WF-003 | Start Create Client wizard from Clients page | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Create Client | on_success: navigates to Create_Client_Wizard
WF-004 | Download client import template | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Download Template | on_success: client Excel template downloaded
WF-005 | Create client via wizard - Submit | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Submit | on_success: creates client in Pending status
WF-006 | Activate Pending client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Pending | terminal: Activate | on_success: client activated; status becomes Active
WF-007 | Edit Pending client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Pending | terminal: Edit | on_success: client details updated
WF-008 | Reject Pending client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Pending | terminal: Reject | on_success: client status set to Rejected
WF-009 | Withdraw Pending client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Pending | terminal: Withdraw | on_success: client status set to Withdrawn
WF-010 | Edit Active client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Edit | on_success: client details updated
WF-011 | Transfer Active client to another office | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Transfer Client | on_success: client transferred to Destination_Office
WF-012 | Close Active client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Close | on_success: client status set to Closed
WF-013 | Add charge to Active client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Add Charge | on_success: charge added to client
WF-014 | Start New Loan for Active client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: New Loan | on_success: navigates to New Loan creation flow
WF-015 | Start New Savings for Active client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: New Savings | on_success: navigates to New Savings creation flow
WF-016 | Start New Share Account for Active client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: New Share Account | on_success: navigates to New Share Account creation flow
WF-017 | Reactivate Closed client | actor: Authenticated user | branch: entity_state == Closed | terminal: Reactivate | on_success: client reactivated; status becomes Active
</workflows>

